  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b89\u0ba3\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbe\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bcb\u0b9a\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd - \u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b89\u0bb2\u0b95 \u0b89\u0ba3\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Food security in highlands at worst - World Food Program in new report",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "6.26 million people in Sri Lanka are food insecure, says the World Food Program in its new report.",
        "The World Food Program has stated that the people of Sri Lanka continue to experience the burden of the economic food crisis, and in its report, three out of ten households are found to be food insecure.",
        "According to the World Food Programme, 6.2 million people are food insecure and 65,600 people are facing severe food insecurity.",
        "According to the World Food Programme, food inflation in June 2022 was 57.4 percent.",
        "The World Food Program reported that the majority of households assessed (61 percent) are taking measures to address food crises, such as reducing the amount of food they eat each day by eating less desirable, less nutritious foods.",
        "The World Food Program also reported that two out of five families do not eat enough food.",
        "Food security is particularly poor in the highlands, where more than half of households are food insecure, and the World Food Program, in its new report, says they face worse outcomes than urban and rural populations in terms of food security and coping strategies.",
        "The UN organization also noted that while urban people are using savings to cope with the current situation, people in the highlands are resorting to loans to buy food and essential items.",
        "About 200,000 families are using emergency livelihood coping strategies that affect their ability to earn an income, the World Food Program said."
      ],
